<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-1501] FileAppender should be able to create files on-demand</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-1501</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;FileAppender should be able to create files lazily.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Add a &lt;tt&gt;createOnDemand=&quot;true|false&quot;&lt;/tt&gt; attribute to &lt;tt&gt;FileAppender&lt;/tt&gt;. The default is &quot;false&quot; for backward compatibility (which we can revisit of course).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If that goes well, do the same for other types file appenders (rolling and random access).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
