                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15411986" author="garydgregory" created="Mon, 8 Aug 2016 15:50:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In Git master.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Reviews welcome &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15412025" author="jvz" created="Mon, 8 Aug 2016 16:15:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;One point of review: why bother adding another huge factory method when you could make a builder instead?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15412056" author="ralph.goers@dslextreme.com" created="Mon, 8 Aug 2016 16:42:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please explain why you deprecated the existing createAppender method and added a new one?  Simply so you didn&apos;t have to update unit tests?  If so then I am -1 on this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15412080" author="jvz" created="Mon, 8 Aug 2016 17:01:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hence why I suggest adding a builder.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15412150" author="garydgregory" created="Mon, 8 Aug 2016 17:47:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I did not want to just update the &lt;tt&gt;createAppender&lt;/tt&gt; API signature, so I added a new API. The old API is all &lt;tt&gt;String&lt;/tt&gt;-based, while the new one is all primitive-based (and String/Object where needed of course). I seems lame that we would not deprecate the String-based API though.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I had forgotten to update all the unit tests to the new API, that is now done. Should the old API be deleted? I know we make no guarantee in Core about BC but I did not want to nuke it right away.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15412156" author="garydgregory" created="Mon, 8 Aug 2016 17:48:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Because it is less work for me ATM.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is there a way to deprecate something to say &quot;Use a builder instead&quot;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15412164" author="garydgregory" created="Mon, 8 Aug 2016 17:56:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;When I look at the ConsoleAppender it has both a builder AND an primitive-based create API. That seems redundant, is that just for BC? Why isn&apos;t the API using the builder to avoid duplicating the validation code? Also the create method checks for a null name but the builder does not. Which one is correct? Bleh, what a mess &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/sad.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; Can we agree one doing things one way?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15412175" author="jvz" created="Mon, 8 Aug 2016 18:02:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The old factories are kept for BC. Also, to deprecate and say &quot;use the builder instead&quot;, I just use the &lt;tt&gt;@deprecated&lt;/tt&gt; javadoc tag.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15412180" author="garydgregory" created="Mon, 8 Aug 2016 18:04:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Let rephrase, should we deprecate &lt;tt&gt;@PluginFactory&lt;/tt&gt; in favor of &lt;tt&gt;@PluginBuilderFactory&lt;/tt&gt;? The bonus being that one can add parameters to a builder without breaking BC.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15412189" author="jvz" created="Mon, 8 Aug 2016 18:08:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t like completely deprecating &lt;tt&gt;@PluginFactory&lt;/tt&gt; because sometimes a plugin only takes 0 or 1 parameters to construct, and a builder is overkill for those.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15412316" author="garydgregory" created="Mon, 8 Aug 2016 19:26:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I added a &lt;tt&gt;Builder&lt;/tt&gt; (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-1505&quot; title=&quot;Create a Builder for FileAppender&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LOG4J2-1505&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LOG4J2-1505&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) and removed the new &lt;tt&gt;createAppender&lt;/tt&gt; method. Reviews welcome.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15412385" author="ralph.goers@dslextreme.com" created="Mon, 8 Aug 2016 20:18:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There is no need for backward compatibility.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15412388" author="ralph.goers@dslextreme.com" created="Mon, 8 Aug 2016 20:19:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I haven&apos;t had a chance to read the documentation that Matt put together on the builders.  I keep using the factory because I understand how it works. I do not think we should have a massive effort to convert all factories to builders.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15412389" author="ralph.goers@dslextreme.com" created="Mon, 8 Aug 2016 20:20:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I will take a peek as soon as I can.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15412394" author="jvz" created="Mon, 8 Aug 2016 20:22:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t want to convert them all to builders as it&apos;s rather tedious. Instead, converting as we add options makes sense.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15412449" author="garydgregory" created="Mon, 8 Aug 2016 20:54:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So we can drop deprecated methods like &lt;tt&gt;org.apache.logging.log4j.core.appender.ConsoleAppender.createAppender(Layout&amp;lt;? extends Serializable&amp;gt;, Filter, String, String, String, String)&lt;/tt&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15414324" author="remkop@yahoo.com" created="Tue, 9 Aug 2016 22:08:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Strictly speaking this isn&apos;t the API module so I see the argument that we can break binary compatibility here, but on the other hand do we &lt;em&gt;have to&lt;/em&gt;? If we can add a builder or factory method with the additional parameter, and let the old method delegate to the new one, there&apos;s no maintenance burden. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The possibility of breaking changes was one reason people mentioned for hesitating to migrate to Log4j 2...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15414485" author="garydgregory" created="Wed, 10 Aug 2016 00:13:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;My plan from now on is to create missing builders when needed and deprecate matching create APIs which I would also recode to use the builder to avoid duplication of validation logic.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15535452" author="remkop@yahoo.com" created="Fri, 30 Sep 2016 08:51:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=garydgregory&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;garydgregory&quot;&gt;garydgregory&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/logging-log4j2/blob/master/src/site/xdoc/manual/appenders.xml#L430&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Appenders documentation&lt;/a&gt;, could you mention the default value for the new &lt;tt&gt;createOnDemand&lt;/tt&gt; attribute?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15539496" author="garydgregory" created="Sun, 2 Oct 2016 01:45:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Remko: In Git master as of yesterday. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
